{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17511295","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17511295"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T12:40:43+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T12:40:43+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11737"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"11737","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/11737"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.09,0.49,0.16,0.2,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4350"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"43986"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"4350","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4350"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11737"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"28974"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"1620"},{"type":"tags","id":"1984"},{"type":"tags","id":"2192"},{"type":"tags","id":"4957"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4966"},{"type":"tags","id":"4976"},{"type":"tags","id":"4984"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11635"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"5986"},{"type":"contributions","id":"6714"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42655"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44363"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"43986","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/43986"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 28-year-old man presents to the Emergency Department (ED) with an open wound on his right arm three hours after fixing an old fence post in the paddock. The patient states that he was fully vaccinated as a child and his last tetanus booster was three years ago. On examination, he has a 6 cm laceration that is heavily contaminated with subcutaneous fat on view. The plan is to perform wound debridement, wash-out, primary closure and to discharge from ED with General Practitioner follow-up.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"In addition to the management plan above, which one of the following is necessary?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["No additional measures required","Flucloxacillin 500 mg PO QID","Cefazolin 2 g IV TDS and Adsorbed diphtheria and tetanus (ADT) vaccine","Flucloxacillin 500 mg PO QID and Tetanus Immunoglobulin","Adsorbed diphtheria and tetanus (ADT) vaccine"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFlucloxacillin 500mg PO QID \u003C/strong\u003Eis the most appropriate response. Careful cleaning and debridement of the wound is the mainstay of treatment, however, prophylactic antibiotic therapy are indicated for wounds that may contain foreign bodies (eg. wood splinters) or be significantly contaminated. In this case they would be recommended for 24 hours for a contaminated wound. \u003Cstrong\u003ENo additional measures required \u003C/strong\u003Eis therefore not the most appropriate response. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECefazolin 2 g IV TDS and Adsorbed diphtheria and tetanus (ADT) vaccine \u003C/strong\u003Eis not the most appropriate response. Whilst prophylactic antibiotics are recommended for this patient, oral antibiotics would be sufficient for this patient. Additionally, an \u003Cstrong\u003Eadsorbed diphtheria and tetanus (ADT) vaccine\u003C/strong\u003E booster is not required as the patient last had a booster less than five years ago.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFlucloxacillin 500mg PO QID and Tetanus Immunoglobulin \u003C/strong\u003Eis not the most appropriate response. Whilst prophylactic antibiotics are indicated, tetanus immunoglobulin is not - it is only indicated if less than three doses of the vaccine have been given and if the wound is anything other than a small and clean wound.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Think of the 3 As for wound management - analgesia, antibiotics (prophylactic), ADT (tetanus prophylaxis)"],"references":["Tetanus. In: The Immunisation Handbook [online]. 2023. Available at: https://immunisationhandbook.health.gov.au/contents/vaccine-preventable-diseases/tetanus","Post-traumatic wound infections. In: Therapeutic Guidelines [online]. 2019; cited 2022 Jun. Available at: https://www.tg.org.au","Prevaldi C, Paolillo C, Locatelli C, Ricci G, Catena F, Ansaloni L, Cervellin G. Management of traumatic wounds in the Emergency Department: position paper from the Academy of Emergency Medicine and Care (AcEMC) and the World Society of Emergency Surgery (WSES). World J Emerg Surg. 2016;;11:30. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27330546/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"28974"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11737"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"28974","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/28974"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-04-03T21:57:45+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-04-03T21:57:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4350"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"43986"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"14","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/14"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udda0","name":"Infectious Diseases","synonyms":["ID"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"u